===Noun===
{{en-plural noun}}

# {{label|en|countable|plural in form|usually|with a plural verb}} A [[tool]] used for [[cut]]ting thin material, consisting of two crossing blades attached at a [[pivot]] point in such a way that the blades slide across each other when the handles are closed.
#: ''Those '''scissors''' are sharp.'' (indicating singular or plural scissors)
#: ''That '''scissors''' is sharp.'' (less commonly to indicate singular scissors)
#: '''''Scissors''' are used to cut the flowers.''
#: ''Use a '''scissors''' to cut them if you don't have proper shears.''
#* {{quote-news|title=Around the Garden|work=New York Times|date=Jun 22, 1947|passage=Roses will last longer if a knife rather than a '''scissors''' is used to cut the blooms.}}
# {{label|en|countable|rugby}} An attacking move conducted by two players; the player without the ball runs from one side of the [[ball carrier]], behind the ball carrier, and receives a [[pass]] from the ball carrier on the other side.
#: ''They executed a perfect '''scissors'''.''
# {{label|en|countable|skating}} A method of skating with one foot significantly in front of the other.
# {{label|en|countable|gymnastics}} An exercise in which the legs are switched back and forth, suggesting the motion of scissors.
# {{label|en|countable|wrestling}} A [[scissors hold]].

====Usage notes====
* "A pair of scissors" is preferred to "a scissors" by about a four-to-one margin in the US ([[COCA]]).
* "The scissors" is preferred to "the scissor" by about a thirty-to-one margin in the US ([[COCA]]).

